  You dropped the events array (and the customHeaders for the shared secret) when you simplified the body — WAHA requires
  events to be a non-empty array from its enum list. Restore both:

  curl -X PUT http://localhost:3000/api/sessions/default \
    -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
    -H "X-Api-Key: dc9cbf430e624d70a5ddf3e57b5ada76" \
    -d '{
      "config": {
        "webhooks": [{
          "url": "http://localhost:8080/api/webhooks/waha",
          "events": ["message"],
          "customHeaders": [{ "name": "X-Webhook-Secret", "value": "dev-webhook-secret-change-me" }]
        }]
      }
    }'

  Without customHeaders, WAHA's webhook calls to our backend won't carry X-Webhook-Secret, and our /api/webhooks/waha
  endpoint will reject them with 401 (per middleware.WebhookSecret in backend/internal/router/router.go) — so both fields
  matter here, not just events.



  Berikut panduan lengkap deploy AYT Sales CRM ke 2 VPS terpisah di IDCloudHost — VPS-A untuk Backend+Frontend+PostgreSQL,
  VPS-B untuk WAHA. Saya sudah cek konfigurasi project ini (.env.example, config.go, webhook_waha.go, docker-compose.yml,
  Dockerfile) supaya nama env var dan endpoint yang saya sebut sesuai kode yang sebenarnya jalan.

  Arsitektur

  [Browser] → HTTPS → [VPS-A: Nginx → Frontend (dist/) + proxy /api → Go backend :8080 → PostgreSQL]
                                                            ↑
                                                webhook X-Webhook-Secret
                                                            ↓
  [WhatsApp] ↔ [VPS-B: Nginx → WAHA :3000 (Docker)] ──POST──┘

  Backend di VPS-A yang memanggil WAHA di VPS-B (kirim pesan), dan WAHA di VPS-B yang memanggil balik backend di VPS-A
  lewat webhook (pesan masuk). Jadi kedua VPS harus saling bisa diakses lewat internet (pakai domain+HTTPS, bukan IP
  lokal).

  ---
  Persiapan di IDCloudHost

  1. Order 2 VPS terpisah (menu Deka Cloud VPS), image Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, spek minimal 2 vCPU/2GB masing-masing.
  2. Catat IP publik masing-masing — misal VPS_A_IP dan VPS_B_IP.
  3. Kalau punya domain, arahkan 2 subdomain lewat DNS panel IDCloudHost (atau registrar lain):
    - app.domainmu.com → VPS_A_IP (CRM)
    - waha.domainmu.com → VPS_B_IP (WAHA)
  4. SSH ke masing-masing VPS pakai root/password dari email provisioning IDCloudHost, lalu ganti password atau pasang SSH
  key.

  ---
  VPS-A — Backend + Frontend + PostgreSQL

  1. Setup dasar server

  sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
  sudo apt install -y curl git build-essential ufw
  sudo ufw allow OpenSSH
  sudo ufw allow 80
  sudo ufw allow 443
  sudo ufw enable

  2. Install Go, Node, PostgreSQL, Nginx

  wget https://go.dev/dl/go1.24.linux-amd64.tar.gz
  sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.24.linux-amd64.tar.gz
  echo 'export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin' >> ~/.bashrc && source ~/.bashrc
  go version

  curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash
  source ~/.bashrc && nvm install 20

  sudo apt install -y postgresql postgresql-contrib nginx
  sudo systemctl enable --now postgresql nginx

  3. Setup database

  sudo -u postgres psql <<EOF
  CREATE USER ayt_user WITH PASSWORD 'ganti-password-kuat';
  CREATE DATABASE ayt_sales OWNER ayt_user;
  GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE ayt_sales TO ayt_user;
  EOF

  4. Clone & konfigurasi backend

  sudo mkdir -p /var/www/ayt-sales && sudo chown $USER /var/www/ayt-sales
  cd /var/www/ayt-sales && git clone <url-repo> .
  cd backend

  Buat .env — ini bagian pentingnya, isi WAHA_BASE_URL/WAHA_API_KEY mengarah ke VPS-B yang akan kamu setup di bawah, dan
  catat WEBHOOK_SECRET karena dipakai lagi nanti di sisi WAHA:

  cat > .env <<EOF
  DB_HOST=localhost
  DB_USER=ayt_user
  DB_PASSWORD=ganti-password-kuat
  DB_NAME=ayt_sales
  DB_PORT=5432
  JWT_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 32)
  PORT=8080
  WEBHOOK_SECRET=$(openssl rand -hex 24)
  WAHA_BASE_URL=https://waha.domainmu.com
  WAHA_API_KEY=ganti-dengan-api-key-waha-vps-b
  WAHA_SESSION=default
  EOF
  cat .env   # simpan WEBHOOK_SECRET & rencanakan WAHA_API_KEY, dipakai lagi di VPS-B

  5. Build & jalankan backend via systemd

  go build -o ayt-backend ./cmd/server
  sudo tee /etc/systemd/system/ayt-backend.service > /dev/null <<'EOF'
  [Unit]
  Description=AYT Sales CRM Backend
  After=network.target postgresql.service

  [Service]
  Type=simple
  User=www-data
  WorkingDirectory=/var/www/ayt-sales/backend
  ExecStart=/var/www/ayt-sales/backend/ayt-backend
  Restart=always
  RestartSec=5
  Environment=GIN_MODE=release

  [Install]
  WantedBy=multi-user.target
  EOF

  sudo chown -R www-data:www-data /var/www/ayt-sales/backend
  sudo systemctl daemon-reload
  sudo systemctl enable --now ayt-backend
  sudo journalctl -u ayt-backend -f   # pastikan "Server running on :8080", lalu Ctrl+C

  6. Build frontend

  cd /var/www/ayt-sales/frontend
  npm install
  npm run build   # output di dist/

  7. Nginx (frontend + proxy /api + proxy webhook publik)

  sudo tee /etc/nginx/sites-available/ayt-sales > /dev/null <<'EOF'
  server {
      listen 80;
      server_name app.domainmu.com;

      root /var/www/ayt-sales/frontend/dist;
      index index.html;

      location / {
          try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;
      }

      location /api/ {
          proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
          proxy_http_version 1.1;
          proxy_set_header Host $host;
          proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
          proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
          proxy_read_timeout 60s;
      }
  }
  EOF
  sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/ayt-sales /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/
  sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx

  8. HTTPS

  sudo apt install -y certbot python3-certbot-nginx
  sudo certbot --nginx -d app.domainmu.com

  Test: buka https://app.domainmu.com, login pakai akun default (admin@ayt.com / admin123 — ganti segera).

